.SH NAME
.PP
printf\-time \- an English & Latin scripture Rosary for TTY and GTK
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]ttyRosary\f[] [\f[B]options\f[]] \-v tag
.PP
\f[B]gtkRosary\f[] [\f[B]options\f[]] \-v tag
.PP
\f[B]ttyBashrc\f[]
.PP
\f[B]manpage\f[]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
printf\-time is a scripture rosary written in C/GCC for the GTK and the
TTY.
It uses both a CSV and a JSON Database.
The CSV contains NAB quotes in English and the JSON contains Vulgate
quotes in Latin.
.SH RESOURCES
.PP
This manual contains instruction on how to use printf\-time.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \f[B]\-v\f[]
Vulgate Latin translation flag.
.RS
.RE
.PP
USECASE EXAMPLE:
.TP
.B \f[B]./ttyRosary \-v\f[]
Use latin biblical readings from the St.\ Jerome's Vulgate.
The Vulgate is stored on a JSON database file.
.RS
.RE
.TP
.B \f[B]./ttyRosary\f[]
Use English biblical readings from the USCCB's New American Bible (NAB).
The NAB is stored on a CSV database file.
.RS
.RE
.TP
.B \f[B]./ttyBashrc\f[]
This display today's liturgical season, feast day information, and
display a season appropriate scripture quote from the rosary database.
It's intended usecase is to display a header text on each new instance a
virtual terminal is launched.
.RS
.RE
